# Snorkel E2E — revision submit must be verified, not assumed

**Incident (May 2026):** `flow:revision:submit` logged `submit_done` and wrote `submitted: true` metadata, but the portal never changed — the card stayed in **Tasks to be revised**, dashboard dates unchanged, and the attached zip reverted to the old file (`cron-sla-reconciler.zip` instead of the uploaded replacement).

## 1. Never treat `Saving...` as a successful Submit

The Snorkel workspace shows **`Saving...`** during autosave (zip upload, rubric edit, checkbox toggles). It appears **before** the Submit button is clicked.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — matches autosave; Playwright passes immediately; CI never runs
await page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Submit' }).click();
await expect(page.getByText(/submitted|saving/i).first()).toBeVisible();

// ✅ GOOD — wait for post-click signals only; exclude bare "Saving..."
await page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Submit' }).click();
await page.waitForFunction(() => {
  const t = document.body?.innerText ?? '';
  return /submitted successfully|submission submitted|evaluation pending|running (checks|evaluation)/i.test(t)
    || (t.includes('Submitted') && !/^Saving\.\.\./m.test(t.split('Submit').pop() ?? ''));
}, null, { timeout: 180_000 });
```

When editing `e2e/lib/revision-flow.ts` or `e2e/lib/submission-flow.ts`, **remove `saving` from submit-success regexes**. Capture page text **after** Submit into the audit log.

## 2. Mandatory post-submit portal verification

After every live revision submit, confirm persistence — do not trust audit `submit_done` alone:

1. Re-open the assignment URL (or home → Revise).
2. Assert the **uploaded zip basename** is visible (not the pre-revision platform zip).
3. Assert the UID is **gone from "Tasks to be revised"** OR dashboard status/date updated.
4. **Redirect to `/home` or `/dashboard` after Submit** (from a `/review` URL) counts as ack — then verify zip on the assignment URL reload.

If verification fails, report **submit did not persist** — not "Evaluation pending".

## 3. Related traps from the same incident

| Trap | Fix |
|------|-----|
| `#` in `SNORKEL_PASSWORD` truncated by dotenv | Quote in `.env`: `SNORKEL_PASSWORD="Terranova#178"` |
| Rubric skipped when task lives under `tasks/old/<slug>/` | Set `SNORKEL_RUBRIC_FILE=tasks/old/<slug>/rubrics.txt` |
| `SNORKEL_UPLOAD_TASK_DIR=../tasks/...` resolves outside repo | Use repo-relative `tasks/<slug>` (no `../`) |
| Stale auth session (wrong Cognito user) | Run `npm run auth:setup` after changing `SNORKEL_EMAIL` |
| `SNORKEL_REVISION_SWAP=1` ignores `SNORKEL_TASK_DIR` | Use `SNORKEL_UPLOAD_TASK_DIR` or set `SNORKEL_REVISION_SWAP=0` |

## 4. Agent checklist before declaring revision complete

- [ ] Submit waiter does **not** match `Saving...` pre-click
- [ ] Rubric path resolved (audit must not show `fill_rubric_skipped` unless intentional)
- [ ] Post-submit portal check: new zip visible + queue/dashboard changed
- [ ] `platform-submission.json` reflects verified portal state, not Playwright assertion alone
